M|Code|tx|Skill for reviewing code changes using the code-rv-graph knowledge graph.
M|Code|tx|Achieves 6.8× fewer tk on reviews by reading only what matters.
M|Step|tx|```
M|Step|tx|get_minimal_context(task="<describe what changed>")
M|Step|tx|```
M|Step|tx|~100 tk. Gives full picture. Do this BEFORE reading any files.
M|Step|tx|```
M|Step|tx|query_graph(target="<specific fn/class>", detail_level="minimal")
M|Step|tx|```
M|Step|tx|Never use broad `list_*` calls. Target specific nodes.
M|Step|tx|```
M|Step|tx|detect_changes()
M|Step|tx|```
M|Step|tx|Returns risk-scored change al. Read the `risk_level` field first.
M|Revi|it|[ ] Does this change break any callers? (check `edge` nodes)
M|Revi|it|[ ] Are tests affected? (check tst coverage nodes)
M|Revi|it|[ ] Are there orphaned imports/functions created by this change?
M|Revi|it|[ ] Does the change match the stated sc criteria?
M|Revi|it|[ ] Is the diff minimal — no unrelated changes?
M|Toke|it|Max 5 tool calls per rv
M|Toke|it|Max 800 tk of graph context
M|Toke|it|`next_tool_suggestions` tells you optimal nx step — follow it
M|Outp|tx|```
